                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d468">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 368.117/303</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Penfield</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 31, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1179. Your 1205, 27th. Ask release Ghiloni upon his sworn statement that he will
                    return immediately United States, and will not leave United States during
                    continuance war. Say Department received positive assurances Ghiloni impressed
                    into Italian army against his will, and upon such assurances Department
                    endeavored obtain his release. Department assured Ghiloni will not revisit Italy
                    during war.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
